-- Nigeria Sold 7.7 Billion Naira of Bills in Open-Market Auction
-- B y   E m e l e   O n u
-- 2012-05-26T10:10:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-26/nigeria-sold-7-7-billion-naira-of-bills-in-open-market-auction.html
Nigeria  sold 7.7 billion naira ($48
million) of Treasury bills in two auctions at its open-market
operations.  The  Central Bank of Nigeria  yesterday sold 3.35 billion
naira of bills comprising 141 million naira of 41-day bills at
13.24 percent and 3.21 billion naira of 55-day debt at 13.40
percent, it said in an e-mailed statement today.  Nigeria also auctioned 4.35 billion naira of short-term
debt comprising 1.83 billion naira of 42-day bills at 13.25
percent and 2.52 billion naira of 56-day debt at 13.40 percent
on May 24, according to the central bank.  Open-market operations are used by the Abuja, Nigeria-based
bank to control short-term interest rate and money supply in the
economy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
